.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-NODE-ID" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-node-id \- print the node's public key (node ID)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-node-id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns only the
.B id
field from
.B lightning-cli getinfo
as a JSON object.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"id":"<33-byte pubkey hex>"}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-alias (1),
.BR lightning-node-network-info (1)
